Exactly these are the people we see today in the images they deliver frantically to the Iranian news agencies. And if from a controlled press one hundred percent state.
I tell you that the Iranian people have many heroes, but Ghasem Soleimani is not among them. Our heroes are Saadi, Hafez, Omar Khayyam, Darius the Great, Kouroush, if we refer to historical examples, and Ali Daei (sportsman) and Asghar Farhadi (director), if we want to come closer to our day.
In Iran, today, you can have no other opinion than the regime. Are you glad Soleimani was murdered, a criminal, a brand representative of a dictatorial regime? We kill you! Are you saying that the Ayatollah of Khamena, the spiritual leader, is an idiot? We kill you! Do you get out on the street that the price of petrol has increased by 300% overnight? We kill you!

This is my country
